  <instructions>
    <step>Chop up the cherry tomatoes into small pieces. Place into a bowl, drizzle over a teaspoon of olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Mix well.</step>
    <step>Toast the slices of bread. Once they are golden brown, take the clove of garlic and rub it over one side of each stice of bread.</step>
    <step>Drizzle the remaining olive oil over the bread.</step>
    <step>Now, spoon the tomatoes on top of the toast. Top with fresh basil leaves if you are using them and dive in immediately.</step>
  </instructions>
